com.pixolus.meterreading

Class ContentRegion

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pixolus.meterreading.ContentRegion

  • public class ContentRegion
extends Object
    Image region that holds content (i.e. a counter) that was detected by the meter reading fragment.

    This class represents a rectangular and possibly rotated image region returned from the counter detection algorithm that represents a counter of a meter. In addition to its actual geometry, it holds information on the relative location compared to a potential second counter (for mechanical double tariff meters), the value of the counter as read by OCR and a numerical representation of the image quality of the rectangular region.

    Use this for debugging or visualization. Never use the value for interpreting the result, but use the MeterReadingResult representation instead.

    All coordinates are to be interpreted as pixel coordinates of an accompanying Bitmap.
